  "summary": "Moderate: ruby security, bug fix, and enhancement update",
  "details": "Ruby is an extensible, interpreted, object-oriented, scripting language. It has features to process text files and to perform system management tasks.\n\nThe following packages have been upgraded to a later upstream version: ruby (3.0.4). (BZ#2109428)\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* Ruby: Double free in Regexp compilation (CVE-2022-28738)\n* Ruby: Buffer overrun in String-to-Float conversion (CVE-2022-28739)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.",
